cs.SP, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.NA 

The paper discusses a new penalty function that promotes sparsity within and across groups, which is a common problem in signal processing. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.SP (Signal Processing), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SI (Sound and Image Processing), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). However, given the focus on signal processing and sparsity, cs.SP is the most likely category. The other categories are also possible because the paper discusses applications in audio processing and exploration seismology, which involve sound and image processing, and the use of convex and nonconvex optimization methods, which are relevant to machine learning and numerical analysis.
